          "description": "Act Despite the Fear",
          "cardNumber": 2,
          "story": "Courage was never the absence of fear; it is the willingness to move while your hands still shake. You do not need to wait until you feel ready, because that calm may never arrive. Take the one small step the fear is asking you to postpone.",
          "caption": "Today's pull: Act Despite the Fear 🌧️. Move while afraid.\n\nWaiting to feel ready can become a way of waiting forever. What if you stepped forward shaking?\nPull your card → @dailycard (link in bio)\n\n#dailycard #courage #wisdom #bravery #takeaction"
